    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cantilevered chair designed in 1928 by Marcel Breuer at the Bauhaus, Dessau. Constructed of bent chromed tubular steel, wood, and cane, it has proved one of the most popular modernist chair designs and remains in production.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
